From 5b39449a9ef0b260a2d9459e2023902606e53eee Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Joseph Magly <1159087+jmagly@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Apr 2026 19:29:44 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 15/25] fix(build): add missing google_benchmark
 buildconfig.gni

This file is imported by WebRTC rtc_base BUILD.gn but was not present
in the M120 gclient sync output. Declares enable_google_benchmarks=false
to satisfy the import without building benchmarks.
---
 third_party/google_benchmark/buildconfig.gni | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 third_party/google_benchmark/buildconfig.gni

diff --git a/third_party/google_benchmark/buildconfig.gni b/third_party/google_benchmark/buildconfig.gni
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000..8bc8df93d0e67
--- /dev/null
+++ b/third_party/google_benchmark/buildconfig.gni
@@ -0,0 +1,8 @@
+# Copyright 2019 The Chromium Authors
+# Use of this source code is governed by a BSD-style license that can be
+# found in the LICENSE file.
+
+declare_args() {
+  # Enable compilation of google_benchmark-based benchmarks.
+  enable_google_benchmarks = false
+}
